description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Research Data Manager within our R&amp;D Performance Team on a 1 year fixed term basis providing secondment cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will work with the R&amp;D governance team, study delivery teams, and the South London CRN team to ensure that research performance data is captured and available for reporting within the Trust and to external organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for using and maintaining databases to support the reporting and presentation of all research metrics that capture performance across R&amp;D that allows queries, reports and data retrieval to be performed in an efficient manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Expectations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain data quality in the EDGE research management system, ensuring that required recruitment data can flow between CPMS and Edge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate and analyse content from multiple data sources to provide timely information for internal decision making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation and submission of internal and external reports, responding to needs of clinical directorates and R&amp;D directors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from those who do not have a formal education qualification but who do have hands on experience working in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the present time the role will be required to work from home multiple days of the week subject to change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, please contact Mark Kilbey, mark.kilbey@gstt.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this vacancy closes on November 8th at midnight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be via MS Teams W/C 16th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMark KilbeyEmail addressmark.kilbey@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
